# One-time data-store adoption — move the EXISTING S3 payload bucket + DynamoDB
# data table into THIS pod's state, so the new module manages the same physical
# resources. NO data copy, NO recreate — only the Terraform state pointer moves.
# This is how every env (dev/stage/prod/Luminary) reuses its existing owned-1
# chat data.
#
# The enabler: set the name-override variables so the module names these two
# resources at their EXISTING physical names — then the import plans as a no-op
# (a rename would force replace = data loss). Everything else keeps cv-gw naming.
#
# ── RUNBOOK (per env, once) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   1. In this pod's tfvars, set the overrides to the existing names, e.g. (dev):
#        dynamodb_table_name    = "codevine-dev-gw-owned-1-data"
#        s3_payload_bucket_name = "codevine-dev-gateway-owned-1-366290348639"
#   2. Copy the two import blocks below into a real `imports.tf` (this .example
#      is ignored by Terraform) with those same ids.
#   3. `terraform plan` — both must show "will be imported" then NO destroy and
#      NO replace (benign tag/config diffs are fine); `terraform apply`.
#   4. Remove them from the OLD owned-1 stack's state so a later owned-1 teardown
#      does NOT destroy them (they are now managed by this pod):
#        terraform state rm module.gateway_pod.aws_dynamodb_table.data
#        terraform state rm module.gateway_pod.aws_s3_bucket.payload
#      (run against the codevine terraform/environments/codevine-<env> stack).
#   5. Delete the import blocks (one-shot). This pod now owns the data stores.
#
# Only these two persistent stores are adopted. Pod identity, secrets, SQS, ALB,
# ECS, IAM, log group are all NEW (created fresh under cv-gw names) — the new pod
# writes to the SAME table/bucket, so chat history is continuous.

# --- DynamoDB data table (all chat data) ---
# import {
#   to = module.gateway.aws_dynamodb_table.data
#   id = "codevine-dev-gw-owned-1-data"
# }

# --- S3 payload bucket (all request/response payloads) ---
# import {
#   to = module.gateway.aws_s3_bucket.payload
#   id = "codevine-dev-gateway-owned-1-366290348639"
# }
